{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"My thing with school lunch is, it's a social justice issue."},{"time":3000,"text":"I'm the Director of Nutrition Services"},{"time":5000,"text":"for the Berkeley Unified School District. I have 90 employees"},{"time":8000,"text":"and 17 locations, 9,600 kids."},{"time":10000,"text":"I'm doing 7,100 meals a day"},{"time":12000,"text":"and I've been doing it for two years,"},{"time":14000,"text":"trying to change how we feed kids in America."},{"time":17000,"text":"And that's what I want to talk to you a little bit about today."},{"time":20000,"text":"These are some of my kids with a salad bar."},{"time":22000,"text":"I put salad bars in all of our schools when I got there."},{"time":24000,"text":"Everyone says it couldn't be done."},{"time":26000,"text":"Little kids couldn't eat off the salad bar,"},{"time":28000,"text":"big kids would spit in it -- neither happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"When I took over this, I tried to really figure out,"},{"time":33000,"text":"like, what my vision would be."},{"time":35000,"text":"How do we really change children's relationship to food?"},{"time":37000,"text":"And I'll tell you why we need to change it,"},{"time":39000,"text":"but we absolutely have to change it."},{"time":41000,"text":"And what I came to understand is,"},{"time":43000,"text":"we needed to teach children"},{"time":45000,"text":"the symbiotic relationship"},{"time":47000,"text":"between a healthy planet, healthy food and healthy kids."},{"time":50000,"text":"And that if we don't do that, the antithesis,"},{"time":53000,"text":"although we've heard otherwise,"},{"time":55000,"text":"is we're really going to become extinct,"},{"time":57000,"text":"because we're feeding our children to death."},{"time":59000,"text":"That's my premise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61000,"text":"We're seeing sick kids get sicker and sicker."},{"time":63000,"text":"And the reason this is happening, by and large,"},{"time":66000,"text":"is because of our food system"},{"time":68000,"text":"and the way the government commodifies food,"},{"time":70000,"text":"the way the government oversees our food,"},{"time":72000,"text":"the way the USDA puts food on kids' plates"},{"time":75000,"text":"that's unhealthy, and allows unhealthy food into schools."},{"time":79000,"text":"And by -- tacitly, all of us send our kids,"},{"time":81000,"text":"or grandchildren, or nieces, or nephews, to school"},{"time":84000,"text":"and tell them to learn, you know,"},{"time":86000,"text":"learn what's in those schools."},{"time":88000,"text":"And when you feed these kids bad food,"},{"time":90000,"text":"that's what they're learning. So that's really what this is all about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"The way we got here is because of big agribusiness."},{"time":97000,"text":"We now live in a country where most of us don't decide,"},{"time":101000,"text":"by and large, what we eat. We see big businesses, Monsanto and DuPont,"},{"time":104000,"text":"who brought out Agent Orange and stain-resistant carpet."},{"time":107000,"text":"They control 90 percent of the commercially produced seeds in our country."},{"time":111000,"text":"These are -- 10 companies"},{"time":113000,"text":"control much of what's in our grocery stores,"},{"time":115000,"text":"much of what people eat. And that's really, really a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119000,"text":"So when I started thinking about these issues"},{"time":121000,"text":"and how I was going to change what kids ate,"},{"time":123000,"text":"I really started focusing on what we would teach them."},{"time":126000,"text":"And the very first thing"},{"time":128000,"text":"was about regional food -- trying to eat food"},{"time":131000,"text":"from within our region."},{"time":133000,"text":"And clearly, with what's going on with fossil fuel usage,"},{"time":135000,"text":"or when -- as the fossil fuel is going away,"},{"time":138000,"text":"as oil hits its peak oil,"},{"time":141000,"text":"you know, we really have to start thinking about whether or not"},{"time":143000,"text":"we should, or could, be moving food"},{"time":146000,"text":"1,500 miles before we eat it."},{"time":149000,"text":"So we talked to kids about that,"},{"time":151000,"text":"and we really start to feed kids regional food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"And then we talk about organic food."},{"time":156000,"text":"Now, most school districts can't really afford organic food,"},{"time":158000,"text":"but we, as a nation,"},{"time":160000,"text":"have to start thinking about"},{"time":162000,"text":"consuming, growing and feeding our children"},{"time":164000,"text":"food that's not chock-full of chemicals."},{"time":166000,"text":"We can't keep feeding our kids pesticides"},{"time":168000,"text":"and herbicides and antibiotics and hormones."},{"time":171000,"text":"We can't keep doing that."},{"time":173000,"text":"You know, it doesn't work."},{"time":175000,"text":"And the results of that are kids getting sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"One of my big soapboxes right now is antibiotics."},{"time":182000,"text":"Seventy percent of all antibiotics consumed in America"},{"time":186000,"text":"is consumed in animal husbandry."},{"time":188000,"text":"We are feeding our kids antibiotics"},{"time":191000,"text":"in beef and other animal protein every day."},{"time":194000,"text":"Seventy percent -- it's unbelievable."},{"time":197000,"text":"And the result of it is, we have diseases."},{"time":200000,"text":"We have things like E. coli that we can't fix,"},{"time":203000,"text":"that we can't make kids better when they get sick."},{"time":207000,"text":"And, you know, certainly antibiotics have been over-prescribed,"},{"time":211000,"text":"but it's an issue in the food supply."},{"time":213000,"text":"One of my favorite facts is that"},{"time":215000,"text":"U.S. agriculture uses 1.2 billion pounds of pesticides every year."},{"time":219000,"text":"That means every one of us, and our children,"},{"time":222000,"text":"consumes what would equal a five-pound bag --"},{"time":224000,"text":"those bags you have at home. If I had one here"},{"time":226000,"text":"and ripped it open,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and that pile I would have on the floor"},{"time":230000,"text":"is what we consume and feed our children every year"},{"time":233000,"text":"because of what goes into our food supply,"},{"time":236000,"text":"because of the way we consume"},{"time":239000,"text":"produce in America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"The USDA allows these antibiotics,"},{"time":243000,"text":"these hormones and these pesticides in our food supply,"},{"time":245000,"text":"and the USDA paid for this ad"},{"time":247000,"text":"in Time magazine."},{"time":249000,"text":"Okay, we could talk about Rachel Carson and DDT,"},{"time":252000,"text":"but we know it wasn't good for you and me."},{"time":254000,"text":"And that is what the USDA allows in our food supply."},{"time":257000,"text":"And that has to change, you know."},{"time":260000,"text":"The USDA cannot be seen as"},{"time":262000,"text":"the be-all and end-all of what we feed"},{"time":265000,"text":"our kids and what's allowed."},{"time":267000,"text":"We cannot believe that they have our best interests at heart."},{"time":270000,"text":"The antithesis of this whole thing is sustainable food."},{"time":273000,"text":"That's what I really try and get people to understand."},{"time":276000,"text":"I really try and teach it to kids. I think it's the most important."},{"time":279000,"text":"It's consuming food in a way"},{"time":281000,"text":"in which we'll still have a planet,"},{"time":283000,"text":"in which kids will grow up to be healthy,"},{"time":285000,"text":"and which really tries to mitigate"},{"time":287000,"text":"all the negative impacts we're seeing."},{"time":290000,"text":"It really is just a new idea."},{"time":292000,"text":"I mean, people toss around sustainability,"},{"time":294000,"text":"but we have to figure out what sustainability is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"In less than 200 years, you know, just in a few generations,"},{"time":299000,"text":"we've gone from being 200 --"},{"time":301000,"text":"being 100 percent, 95 percent farmers"},{"time":304000,"text":"to less than 2 percent of farmers."},{"time":306000,"text":"We now live in a country that has more prisoners than farmers --"},{"time":309000,"text":"2.1 million prisoners, 1.9 million farmers."},{"time":313000,"text":"And we spend 35,000 dollars"},{"time":315000,"text":"on average a year keeping a prisoner in prison,"},{"time":317000,"text":"and school districts spend 500 dollars a year"},{"time":321000,"text":"feeding a child."},{"time":323000,"text":"It's no wonder, you know, we have criminals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":327000,"text":"And what's happening is, we're getting sick."},{"time":330000,"text":"We're getting sick and our kids are getting sick."},{"time":334000,"text":"It is about what we feed them."},{"time":337000,"text":"What goes in is what we are."},{"time":339000,"text":"We really are what we eat."},{"time":341000,"text":"And if we continue down this path,"},{"time":343000,"text":"if we continue to feed kids bad food,"},{"time":345000,"text":"if we continue not to teach them what good food is,"},{"time":350000,"text":"what's going to happen? You know, what is going to happen?"},{"time":353000,"text":"What's going to happen to our whole medical system?"},{"time":356000,"text":"What's going to happen is,"},{"time":358000,"text":"we're going to have kids"},{"time":360000,"text":"that have a life less long than our own."},{"time":363000,"text":"The CDC, the Center for Disease Control,"},{"time":366000,"text":"has said, of the children born in the year 2000 --"},{"time":368000,"text":"those seven- and eight-year-olds today --"},{"time":370000,"text":"one out of every three Caucasians,"},{"time":372000,"text":"one out of every two African-Americans and Hispanics"},{"time":375000,"text":"are going to have diabetes in their lifetime."},{"time":379000,"text":"And if that's not enough, they've gone on to say,"},{"time":382000,"text":"most before they graduate high school."},{"time":384000,"text":"This means that 40 or 45 percent"},{"time":388000,"text":"of all school-aged children"},{"time":390000,"text":"could be insulin-dependent"},{"time":392000,"text":"within a decade. Within a decade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396000,"text":"What's going to happen?"},{"time":398000,"text":"Well, the CDC has gone further to say"},{"time":400000,"text":"that those children born in the year 2000"},{"time":402000,"text":"could be the first generation"},{"time":404000,"text":"in our country's history to die at a younger age than their parents."},{"time":407000,"text":"And it's because of what we feed them."},{"time":409000,"text":"Because eight-year-olds don't get to decide --"},{"time":411000,"text":"and if they do, you should be in therapy."},{"time":414000,"text":"You know, we are responsible"},{"time":416000,"text":"for what kids eat."},{"time":418000,"text":"But oops, maybe they're responsible for what kids eat."},{"time":422000,"text":"Big companies spend 20 billion dollars a year"},{"time":425000,"text":"marketing non-nutrient foods to kids."},{"time":428000,"text":"20 billion dollars a year. 10,000 ads most kids see."},{"time":432000,"text":"They spend 500 dollars"},{"time":434000,"text":"for every one dollar -- 500 dollars marketing foods"},{"time":437000,"text":"that kids shouldn't eat for every one dollar"},{"time":440000,"text":"marketing healthy, nutritious food."},{"time":442000,"text":"The result of which is kids think they're going to die"},{"time":444000,"text":"if they don't have chicken nuggets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446000,"text":"You know that everybody thinks they should be eating more, and more, and more."},{"time":449000,"text":"This is the USDA portion size, that little, tiny thing."},{"time":452000,"text":"And the one over there, that's bigger than my head,"},{"time":454000,"text":"is what McDonald's and Burger King"},{"time":457000,"text":"and those big companies think we should eat."},{"time":458000,"text":"And why can they serve that much?"},{"time":460000,"text":"Why can we have 29-cent Big Gulps"},{"time":463000,"text":"and 99-cent double burgers?"},{"time":465000,"text":"It's because of the way the government commodifies food,"},{"time":468000,"text":"and the cheap corn and cheap soy"},{"time":470000,"text":"that are pushed into our food supply"},{"time":472000,"text":"that makes these non-nutrient foods"},{"time":474000,"text":"really, really cheap."},{"time":476000,"text":"Which is why I say it's a social justice issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"Now, I said I'm doing this in Berkeley, and you might think,"},{"time":481000,"text":"\"Oh, Berkeley. Of course you can do it in Berkeley.\""},{"time":483000,"text":"Well, this is the food I found 24 months ago."},{"time":486000,"text":"This is not even food."},{"time":488000,"text":"This is the stuff we were feeding our kids: Extremo Burritos,"},{"time":490000,"text":"corn dogs,"},{"time":492000,"text":"pizza pockets, grilled cheese sandwiches."},{"time":494000,"text":"Everything came in plastic, in cardboard."},{"time":497000,"text":"The only kitchen tools my staff had was a box cutter."},{"time":500000,"text":"The only working piece of equipment in my kitchen"},{"time":502000,"text":"was a can crusher, because if it didn't come in a can,"},{"time":505000,"text":"it came frozen in a box."},{"time":507000,"text":"The USDA allows this."},{"time":509000,"text":"The USDA allows all of this stuff."},{"time":511000,"text":"In case you can't tell, that's, like,"},{"time":513000,"text":"pink Danish and some kind of cupcakes."},{"time":517000,"text":"Chicken nuggets, Tater Tots, chocolate milk with high fructose,"},{"time":520000,"text":"canned fruit cocktail -- a reimbursable meal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"That's what the government says is okay to feed our kids."},{"time":527000,"text":"It ain't okay. You know what? It is not okay."},{"time":531000,"text":"And we, all of us,"},{"time":533000,"text":"have to understand"},{"time":535000,"text":"that this is about us,"},{"time":537000,"text":"that we can make a difference here."},{"time":539000,"text":"Now I don't know if any of you out there invented chicken nuggets,"},{"time":541000,"text":"but I'm sure you're rich if you did."},{"time":543000,"text":"But whoever decided that a chicken should look like"},{"time":546000,"text":"a heart, a giraffe, a star?"},{"time":550000,"text":"Well, Tyson did, because there's no chicken in the chicken."},{"time":553000,"text":"And that they could figure it out,"},{"time":555000,"text":"that we could sell this stuff to kids."},{"time":557000,"text":"You know, what's wrong with teaching kids"},{"time":559000,"text":"that chicken looks like chicken?"},{"time":561000,"text":"But this is what most schools serve."},{"time":563000,"text":"In fact, this may be what a lot of parents serve,"},{"time":566000,"text":"as opposed to -- this is what we try and serve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569000,"text":"We really need to change"},{"time":571000,"text":"this whole paradigm with kids and food."},{"time":574000,"text":"We really have to teach children"},{"time":576000,"text":"that chicken is not a giraffe."},{"time":579000,"text":"You know, that vegetables"},{"time":581000,"text":"are actually colorful, that they have flavor,"},{"time":584000,"text":"that carrots grow in the ground,"},{"time":587000,"text":"that strawberries grow in the ground."},{"time":589000,"text":"There's not a strawberry tree or a carrot bush."},{"time":592000,"text":"You know, we have to change"},{"time":595000,"text":"the way we teach kids about these things."},{"time":597000,"text":"There's a lot of stuff we can do. There's a lot of schools"},{"time":600000,"text":"doing farm-to-school programs. There's a lot of schools"},{"time":603000,"text":"actually getting fresh food into schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606000,"text":"Now, in Berkeley, we've gone totally fresh."},{"time":609000,"text":"We have no high-fructose corn syrup,"},{"time":611000,"text":"no trans fats, no processed foods."},{"time":613000,"text":"We're cooking from scratch every day."},{"time":615000,"text":"We have 25 percent of our --"},{"time":618000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":620000,"text":"thank you -- 25 percent of our stuff"},{"time":622000,"text":"is organic and local. We cook."},{"time":624000,"text":"Those are my hands. I get up at 4 a.m."},{"time":627000,"text":"every day and go cook the food for the kids,"},{"time":630000,"text":"because this is what we need to do."},{"time":632000,"text":"We can't keep serving kids"},{"time":634000,"text":"processed crap,"},{"time":636000,"text":"full of chemicals,"},{"time":638000,"text":"and expect these are going to be healthy citizens."},{"time":640000,"text":"You're not going to get the next generation,"},{"time":643000,"text":"or the generation after, to be able to think like this"},{"time":645000,"text":"if they're not nourished."},{"time":647000,"text":"If they're eating"},{"time":649000,"text":"chemicals all the time,"},{"time":651000,"text":"they're not going to be able to think."},{"time":653000,"text":"They're not going to be smart."},{"time":655000,"text":"You know what? They're just going to be sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658000,"text":"Now one of the things that -- what happened when I went into Berkeley"},{"time":660000,"text":"is I realized that, you know, this was all pretty amazing to people,"},{"time":663000,"text":"very, very different, and I needed to market it."},{"time":666000,"text":"I came up with these calendars that I sent home to every parent."},{"time":669000,"text":"And these calendars really started to lay out my program."},{"time":672000,"text":"Now I'm in charge of all the cooking classes"},{"time":674000,"text":"and all the gardening classes in our school district."},{"time":677000,"text":"So this is a typical menu."},{"time":679000,"text":"This is what we're serving this week at the schools."},{"time":681000,"text":"And you see these recipes on the side?"},{"time":683000,"text":"Those are the recipes that the kids learn in my cooking classes."},{"time":685000,"text":"They do tastings of these ingredients in the gardening classes."},{"time":689000,"text":"They also may be growing them. And we serve them in the cafeterias."},{"time":693000,"text":"If we're going to change children's relationship to food,"},{"time":695000,"text":"it's delicious, nutritious food in the cafeterias,"},{"time":698000,"text":"hands-on experience -- you're looking in cooking and gardening classes --"},{"time":701000,"text":"and academic curriculum to tie it all together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"Now you've probably garnered that I don't love the USDA,"},{"time":708000,"text":"and I don't have any idea what to do with their pyramid,"},{"time":711000,"text":"this upside-down pyramid with a rainbow over the top, I don't know."},{"time":713000,"text":"You know, run up into the end of the rainbow,"},{"time":715000,"text":"I don't know what you do with it. So, I came up with my own."},{"time":718000,"text":"This is available on my website in English and Spanish,"},{"time":720000,"text":"and it's a visual way to talk to kids about food."},{"time":723000,"text":"The really tiny hamburger, the really big vegetables."},{"time":726000,"text":"We have to start changing this."},{"time":728000,"text":"We have to make kids understand"},{"time":731000,"text":"that their food choices make a big difference."},{"time":735000,"text":"We have cooking classes -- we have cooking classrooms in our schools."},{"time":738000,"text":"And why this is so important is"},{"time":740000,"text":"that we now have grown a generation,"},{"time":743000,"text":"maybe two, of kids where one out of every four meals"},{"time":746000,"text":"is eaten in fast food, one of every four meals is eaten in a car"},{"time":750000,"text":"and one out of every last four meals is eaten in front of a TV or computer."},{"time":754000,"text":"What are kids learning? Where is the family time?"},{"time":758000,"text":"Where is socialization? Where is discussion?"},{"time":762000,"text":"Where is learning to talk?"},{"time":764000,"text":"You know, we have to change it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"I work with kids a lot. These are kids I work with in Harlem."},{"time":769000,"text":"EATWISE -- Enlightened and Aware Teens Who Inspire Smart Eating."},{"time":772000,"text":"We have to teach kids"},{"time":774000,"text":"that Coke and Pop Tarts"},{"time":776000,"text":"aren't breakfast."},{"time":778000,"text":"We have to teach kids that if they're on a diet"},{"time":780000,"text":"of refined sugar,"},{"time":782000,"text":"they go up and down, just like if they're on a diet of crack."},{"time":787000,"text":"And we have to pull it all together. We have composting in all of our schools."},{"time":790000,"text":"We have recycling in all of our schools."},{"time":792000,"text":"You know, the things that we maybe do at home"},{"time":794000,"text":"and think are so important,"},{"time":796000,"text":"we have to teach kids about in school."},{"time":800000,"text":"It has to be so much a part of them"},{"time":802000,"text":"that they really get it."},{"time":804000,"text":"Because, you know what, many of us"},{"time":806000,"text":"are sort of at the end of our careers,"},{"time":808000,"text":"and we need to be giving these kids --"},{"time":810000,"text":"these young kids, the next generation --"},{"time":812000,"text":"the tools to save themselves"},{"time":814000,"text":"and save the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816000,"text":"One of the things I do a lot is public-private partnerships."},{"time":819000,"text":"I work with private companies"},{"time":821000,"text":"who are willing to do R &amp; D with me,"},{"time":823000,"text":"who are willing to do distribution for me,"},{"time":825000,"text":"who are really willing to work to go into schools."},{"time":827000,"text":"Schools are underfunded."},{"time":829000,"text":"Most schools in America spend less"},{"time":831000,"text":"than 7,500 dollars a year teaching a child."},{"time":834000,"text":"That comes down to under five dollars an hour."},{"time":837000,"text":"Most of you spend 10, 15 dollars an hour"},{"time":839000,"text":"for babysitters when you have them."},{"time":842000,"text":"So we're spending less than 5 dollars an hour on the educational system."},{"time":845000,"text":"And if we're going to change it,"},{"time":847000,"text":"and change how we feed kids,"},{"time":849000,"text":"we really have to rethink that."},{"time":851000,"text":"So, public and private partnerships,"},{"time":853000,"text":"advocacy groups, working with foundations."},{"time":856000,"text":"In our school district, the way we afford this"},{"time":858000,"text":"is our school district allocates .03 percent"},{"time":861000,"text":"of the general fund"},{"time":863000,"text":"towards nutrition services. And I think if every school district"},{"time":866000,"text":"allocated a half to one percent,"},{"time":868000,"text":"we could start to really fix this program."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871000,"text":"We really need to change it."},{"time":874000,"text":"It's going to take more money."},{"time":876000,"text":"Of course, it's not all about food; it's also about"},{"time":878000,"text":"kids getting exercise."},{"time":880000,"text":"And one of the simple things we can do"},{"time":882000,"text":"is put recess before lunch."},{"time":884000,"text":"It's sort of this \"duh\" thing."},{"time":886000,"text":"You know, if you have kids coming into lunch"},{"time":888000,"text":"and all they're going to do when they get out of lunch is go to have recess,"},{"time":891000,"text":"you see them just throw away their lunch so they can run outside."},{"time":894000,"text":"And then, at one in the afternoon, they're totally crashing."},{"time":897000,"text":"These are your children and grandchildren that are totally melting down"},{"time":899000,"text":"when you pick them up, because they haven't had lunch."},{"time":901000,"text":"So if the only thing they'd have to do after lunch is go to class,"},{"time":904000,"text":"believe me, they're going to sit there and eat their lunch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907000,"text":"We need to --"},{"time":909000,"text":"we need to educate."},{"time":911000,"text":"We need to educate the kids."},{"time":913000,"text":"We need to educate the staff."},{"time":915000,"text":"I had 90 employees."},{"time":917000,"text":"Two were supposed to be cooks -- none could."},{"time":919000,"text":"And, you know, I'm not that better off now."},{"time":922000,"text":"But we really have to educate."},{"time":924000,"text":"We have to get academic institutions to start thinking"},{"time":927000,"text":"about ways to teach people how to cook again,"},{"time":930000,"text":"because, of course, they don't --"},{"time":932000,"text":"because we've had this processed food in schools"},{"time":934000,"text":"and institutions for so long."},{"time":936000,"text":"We need 40-minute lunches --"},{"time":938000,"text":"most schools have 20-minute lunches --"},{"time":940000,"text":"and lunches that are time-appropriate."},{"time":942000,"text":"There was just a big study done, and so many schools"},{"time":944000,"text":"are starting lunch at nine and 10 in the morning."},{"time":946000,"text":"That is not lunchtime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949000,"text":"You know, it's crazy. It's crazy what we're doing."},{"time":952000,"text":"And just remember,"},{"time":954000,"text":"at very least tacitly,"},{"time":956000,"text":"this is what we're teaching children"},{"time":959000,"text":"as what they should be doing."},{"time":961000,"text":"I think if we're going to fix this,"},{"time":963000,"text":"one of the things we have to do"},{"time":965000,"text":"is really change how we have oversight"},{"time":967000,"text":"over the National School Lunch Program."},{"time":969000,"text":"Instead of the National School Lunch Program being under the USDA,"},{"time":972000,"text":"I think it should be under CDC."},{"time":974000,"text":"If we started to think about food"},{"time":977000,"text":"and how we feed our kids"},{"time":979000,"text":"as a health initiative,"},{"time":982000,"text":"and we started thinking about food as health,"},{"time":985000,"text":"then I think we wouldn't have corn dogs"},{"time":988000,"text":"as lunch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":990000,"text":"Okay, Finance 101 on this,"},{"time":993000,"text":"and this -- I'm sort of wrapping it up with this finance piece,"},{"time":996000,"text":"because I think this is something we all have to understand."},{"time":999000,"text":"The National School Lunch Program spends 8 billion dollars"},{"time":1001000,"text":"feeding 30 million children a year."},{"time":1003000,"text":"That number probably needs to double."},{"time":1005000,"text":"People say, \"Oh my God, where are we going to get 8 billion?\""},{"time":1008000,"text":"In this country, we're spending 110 billion dollars a year"},{"time":1012000,"text":"on fast food."},{"time":1015000,"text":"We spend 100 billion dollars a year"},{"time":1017000,"text":"on diet aids."},{"time":1019000,"text":"We spend 50 billion dollars on vegetables,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"which is why we need all the diet aids."},{"time":1024000,"text":"We spend 200 billion dollars a year"},{"time":1027000,"text":"on diet-related illness today,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"with nine percent of our kids having type 2 diabetes."},{"time":1033000,"text":"200 billion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035000,"text":"So you know what, when we talk"},{"time":1037000,"text":"about needing 8 billion more, it's not a lot."},{"time":1040000,"text":"That 8 billion comes down to two dollars and 49 cents --"},{"time":1043000,"text":"that's what the government allocates for lunch."},{"time":1046000,"text":"Most school districts spend two thirds of that on payroll and overhead."},{"time":1049000,"text":"That means we spend less than a dollar a day"},{"time":1052000,"text":"on food for kids in schools --"},{"time":1054000,"text":"most schools, 80 to 90 cents. In L.A., it's 56 cents."},{"time":1059000,"text":"So we're spending less than a dollar, OK, on lunch."},{"time":1062000,"text":"Now I don't know about you,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"but I go to Starbucks and Pete's and places like that,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"and venti latte in San Francisco is five dollars."},{"time":1069000,"text":"One gourmet coffee,"},{"time":1071000,"text":"one, is more --"},{"time":1073000,"text":"we spend more on than we are spending to feed kids"},{"time":1076000,"text":"for an entire week"},{"time":1079000,"text":"in our schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081000,"text":"You know what? We should be ashamed."},{"time":1085000,"text":"We, as a country, should be ashamed"},{"time":1088000,"text":"at that."},{"time":1090000,"text":"The richest country."},{"time":1092000,"text":"In our country,"},{"time":1094000,"text":"it's the kids that need it the most,"},{"time":1097000,"text":"who get this really, really lousy food."},{"time":1099000,"text":"It's the kids who have parents and grandparents"},{"time":1101000,"text":"and uncles and aunts that can't even afford"},{"time":1105000,"text":"to pay for school lunch that gets this food."},{"time":1108000,"text":"And those are the same kids"},{"time":1110000,"text":"who are going to be getting sick."},{"time":1113000,"text":"Those are the same kids who we should be taking care of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116000,"text":"We can all make a difference."},{"time":1119000,"text":"That every single one of us,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"whether we have children,"},{"time":1123000,"text":"whether we care about children, whether we have nieces or nephews,"},{"time":1126000,"text":"or anything --"},{"time":1128000,"text":"that we can make a difference."},{"time":1130000,"text":"Whether you sit down and eat a meal with your kids,"},{"time":1132000,"text":"whether you take your kids, or grandchildren,"},{"time":1134000,"text":"or nieces and nephews shopping"},{"time":1137000,"text":"to a farmers' market. Just do tastings with them."},{"time":1140000,"text":"Sit down and care."},{"time":1142000,"text":"And on the macro level,"},{"time":1144000,"text":"we're in what seems to be"},{"time":1146000,"text":"a 19-month presidential campaign,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"and of all the things we're asking"},{"time":1152000,"text":"all of these potential leaders,"},{"time":1154000,"text":"what about asking for the health of our children?"},{"time":1156000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}